## Key Insights
1. TV2's balance is hard to beat — deviating in ANY direction hurts
2. All top3 converge to ~7.5 in tournament with 81 matches
3. Map variance is DOMINANT factor (1.28-4.33 across seeds)
4. 72% of aligner time is idle-scrambling (frontier=0)
5. Junction discovery limited to ~14/65 per team in self-play
6. Capture targeting = TV2 in self-play (symmetric benefit)
7. Clips faction competes for junctions — relevant for tournament
8. Exploration helps on good maps (+4%) but hurts on bad maps (-35%)
9. Current heuristic ceiling appears to be ~7.5

